               ],
               "death": null
            },
            {
               "id": "c7442d8a-e853-4e3f-9558-3901c35f8fc6",
               "name": "Anastacia",
               "surname": "Maria de Jesus",
               "patronymic": "",
               "fullname": "Anastacia Maria de Jesus",
               "sex": "feminine",
               "gender": "feminine",
               "is_real": true,
               "haplogroup": null,
               "history": [
                  {
                     "text": "Although the exact date of Anastacia's baptism is unknown, records suggest that she was likely baptized on <span class=\"htdate\"></span>",
                     "source": [
                        {
                           "type": 0,
                           "uuid": "e22c0cda-295d-42b6-b10b-5b2afa7640fd",
                           "text": "Arquivo Eclesiástico da Arquidiocese de Mariana"
                        }
                     ],
                     "date_time": null,
                     "isTable": false,
                     "format": "",
                     "PostMention": ""
                  },
                  {
                     "text": "After her birth, Anastacia continued as enslaved (<i>\"cativa\"</i>) at least until <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, when she is documented as being 7 years old",
                     "source": [
                        {
                           "type": 0,
                           "uuid": "a69983fe-0955-4b34-bdc2-be1dcdef4b3e",
                           "text": "Arquivo Público Mineiro, <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, fogos 9"
                        }
                     ],
                     "date_time": null,
                     "isTable": false,
                     "format": "",
                     "PostMention": ""
                  },
                  {
                     "text": "Due to a lack of documentation, we cannot specify exactly when she gained her freedom, but according to the population map (<i>\"mapa de população\"</i>) from <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, Anastacia was sixteen years old, appears married, and free, living in the house of her former \"owner\"",
                     "source": [
                        {
                           "type": 0,
                           "uuid": "8bb30e39-0316-4258-94cc-fb8e0415c4d0",
                           "text": "Arquivo Público Mineiro, <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, fogos 22"
                        }
                     ],
                     "date_time": null,
                     "isTable": false,
                     "format": "",
                     "PostMention": ""
                  },
                  {
                     "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>The question of freedom</b><br />The population maps indicate that Maria Úrsula owned several dozen enslaved people but granted freedom to Anastacia, who continued living in her house. Was this a benevolent act? Did her husband buy her freedom? Was it a way to avoid paying taxes? Can you propose another hypothesis to explain her emancipation?</div></div></center>",
                     "source": null,
                     "date_time": null,
                     "isTable": false,
                     "format": "html",
                     "PostMention": "."
                  },
                  {
                     "text": "In the population map from <span class=\"htdate\"></span> Anastacia, now was 24 years old, her husband, and their children are recorded as living in their own household",
                     "source": [
                        {
                           "type": 0,
                           "uuid": "9a78ca27-3f9d-48a2-ba49-0139361f780b",
                           "text": "Arquivo Público Mineiro, <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, fogos 83"
                        }
                     ],
                     "date_time": null,
                     "isTable": false,
                     "format": "",
                     "PostMention": ""
                  },
                  {
                     "text": "Anastacia passed away on <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, at the age of 61 years old in Cachoeira do Campo",
                     "source": [
                        {
                           "type": 0,
                           "uuid": "f6b98da1-a72a-4519-bd71-ed4eeb7142da",
                           "text": "Family Search, <i>Cachoeira do Campo</i>"
                        }
                     ],
                     "date_time": null,
                     "isTable": false,
                     "format": "",
                     "PostMention": ""
                  },
                  {
                     "text": "When we examine the documents where Anastacia is mentioned, we find inconsistencies in her recorded ages:</p><p><ul><li>Population map of <span class=\"htdate\"></span>: She is listed as 7 years old, suggesting a birth year around <span class=\"htdate\"></span>.</li><li>Population map of <span class=\"htdate\"></span>: She is 16 years old, indicating a birth year of approximately <span class=\"htdate\"></span>.</li><li>Population map of <span class=\"htdate\"></span>: She is 24 years old, pointing to a birth year around <span class=\"htdate\"></span>.</li><li>Death record <span class=\"htdate\"></span>: She is recorded as 61 years old, which suggests a birth year of <span class=\"htdate\"></span>.</li></ul></p><p>These discrepancies may be due to various factors, such as the lack of official civil registration in Brazil during her lifetime and the fact that Anastacia was enslaved",
                     "source": null,
                     "date_time": null,
                     "isTable": false,
                     "format": "html",
                     "PostMention": "."
                  },
                  {
                     "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\" style=\"background-color: #D7FFE4;\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\" style=\"background-color: #D7FFE4;\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-infinity\" style=\"font-size: 1em;\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\" style=\"background-color: #D7FFE4;\"><b>Mathematics in History</b><br />In the 19th century, according to the Gregorian calendar, baptismal records often did not include surnames. As a result, linking an individual to their parents often required other documents, such as marriage records or inventories. In the absence of these documents, we can use mathematical concepts, like limits (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('18a901e4-3da3-45d8-a239-fb551e78698e'); return false;\">Limites naturais</a>), to estimate relationships, though not to confirm them definitively.<br /><br />Although we do not have Anastacia's exact baptism record, we do have the maximum limit of her life—her death date on <span class=\"htdate\"></span>. This information can guide us in searching for other documents that might confirm the dates and provide additional evidence.<br /><br />The population maps provide the following insights:<br /><br /> <b><span class=\"htdate\"></span></b>: The age listed is consistent with her death record.<br /><b><span class=\"htdate\"></span></b>: While the age differs slightly, the document confirms her marriage and residence.<br /><b><span class=\"htdate\"></span></b>:  A person named Anastacia is recorded living in the same household as in the later maps, but her age differs significantly from what is expected.<br /><br />Based on this information, we can establish a timeframe between <span class=\"htdate\"></span> and <span class=\"htdate\"></span> to search for a baptism record that might identify Anastacia's parents. In this research, we discovered a baptism record for an Anastacia on September <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, daughter of Joaquina \"Cabra\". Both were enslaved by Maria Úrsula da Silva, as indicated in the population maps.</div></div></center>",
                     "source": null,
                     "date_time": null,
                     "isTable": false,
                     "format": "html",
                     "PostMention": "."
                  },
                  {
                     "text": "Given the available evidence and using the concept of mathematical limits, we can reasonably infer that Anastacia, daughter of Joaquina \"Cabra\", both enslaved by Maria Úrsula da Silva, is likely the same person who married Bento Dias da Silva",
                     "source": null,
                     "date_time": null,
                     "isTable": false,
                     "format": "html",
                     "PostMention": "."
                  },
                  {
                     "text": "In addition to the data presented here related to her ancestry, we would also like to highlight the fact that Anastácia received part of the will of Carlos Moreira Murta, known as 'Terça'",
                     "source": [
                        {
                           "type": 0,
                           "uuid": "147e96d0-7968-4218-bd01-0baaa66098c1",
                           "text": "Family Search"
                        }
