   "exercise_v2": [
      {
         "question": "Is researching enslaved ancestors as simple as researching royal ancestors?",
         "yesNoAnswer": "No",
         "additionalInfo": "The reason a person became a king or was enslaved is connected to various historical events. However, regardless of a person's social position, it is undeniable that we all belong to the same species, Homo sapiens. Despite the lack of natural differences, social status greatly impacts the ability to trace ancestral connections."
      },
      {
         "question": "Did the freedom of enslaved people in Brazil occur only after the Eusébio de Queiroz law in 1850 (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('52dbf4d6-a772-451e-b408-2f386dfa57bf'); return false;\">Graden, D. T., <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a>)?",
         "yesNoAnswer": "No",
         "additionalInfo": "Laws began to force slave owners to change, but the official end of the slavery system required more than three decades. The liberation of enslaved individuals like Anastacia was more likely an exception rather than a common occurrence in the first decades of the 19th century. This is why we propose a reflection on this matter."
      }
